A cruise the week of April 21 through Royal Carribean for 2 people is $2,451 (balcony room). On their site they widely let people know that kids sail for free. However, once you add a kid to this equation - the total price goes up to $8,196!!!!!!!!!! That is $5,745 more for the exact same room to add a “free child”
So what this means is an adult cost is $1039 per person while a child costs $5,745…
It would be cheaper to book 2 of the same rooms for 4 adults
When you call and ask them about this they will say “oh no it’s because the room is different
You will then say, no the room is exactly the same—
They will say oh no but the couch pulls out when you add a child. Even if that is true- you’re telling me it’s almost $6,000 for a couch that pulls out??

How are they getting away with this nonsense?
